@startuml
title Viaverse Analytics / Observability — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nproduct events\ncrash/session\nweb vitals" as Client
component "API Gateway\ncorrelationId\ntraceparent\nrate limit" as Gateway
component "Spring Boot Services\nMicrometer\nOpenTelemetry\nstructured logs" as Services
component "analytics-service\nevent ingestion\nschema validation\nfunnel/cohort" as Analytics
component "OpenTelemetry Collector\ntraces\nmetrics\nlogs routing" as Collector
database "Prometheus + Perses\nmetrics\nSLO dashboards\nalerts" as Prom
database "Jaeger\ndistributed traces" as Jaeger
database "OpenSearch\nstructured logs\nanalytics index" as Logs
database "Analytics Warehouse\nprivacy-safe events\nfunnels/cohorts" as Warehouse
component "Alertmanager / Ops\nSLO breach\nerror budget\nanomaly" as Alerts
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nProductEvent\nDataQualityFailed\nAlertRaised" as Kafka

Client --> Gateway : HTTPS + trace context
Gateway --> Services : service calls
Client --> Analytics : product events
Services --> Collector : OTel export
Collector --> Prom : metrics
Collector --> Jaeger : traces
Collector --> Logs : logs
Analytics --> Warehouse : privacy-safe events
Analytics --> Kafka : quality/events
Prom --> Alerts : SLO alerts
Logs --> Alerts : error anomalies

note bottom
Operational observability and product analytics are related but separated.
Product analytics requires consent/governance;
observability requires redaction and secret filtering.
end note
@enduml
